
[1]millenium

   MILLEN'IUM, n. [L. mille, a thousand, and annus, year.]

   A thousand years; a word used to denote the thousand years mentioned in
   Revelations 20. during which period Satan shall be bound and restrained
   from seducing men to sin, and Christ shall reign on earth with his
   saints.
